  "prompt": "Where do we get beef jerky or biltong in London?",
  "response": "In London, you have several options for purchasing beef jerky or biltong:\n\n1. **Specialty Shops and Delis:** \n   - **The Savanna:** Specializes in South African products including biltong. They have several locations across London.\n   - **Jerky House:** Known for a variety of jerky options, offering a wide range of flavors and meat types.\n  \n2. **Markets:**\n   - **Borough Market:** Known for its diverse food offerings, some stalls sell specialty meats, including biltong and jerky.\n   - **Spitalfields Market and Camden Market:** These markets often have vendors selling artisanal and gourmet food products, including jerky and biltong.\n\n3. **Supermarkets:**\n   - Larger supermarkets such as **Tesco**, **Sainsbury\u2019s**, and **Waitrose** often carry packets of beef jerky in their snack or meat sections.\n   - **Whole Foods Market:** Known for its organic and specialty food items, carries a variety of jerky options.\n\n4. **Online Retailers:**\n   - Websites like **Amazon UK**, **The British Jerky Co., and **Biltong Direct** offer a range of products that can be conveniently delivered.\n\n5. **Health and Gourmet Shops:**\n   - Stores like **Holland & Barrett** offer health-focused snack options, including beef jerky and sometimes biltong.\n   - **Planet Organic:** Offers organic and natural food items, including healthier jerky options.\n\nWhen searching for these products, consider trying different flavors and styles to find the one you prefer.",
